task.summary: Default task

Finished authentication. Made a filter that authenticates all incoming requests by checking their JWT with the users in the database. Made a facility to update user details. Made a facility to update passwords and require old password too. All that is left (which is small), is issue new token after update where username has changed. Can start work on site api now

Added API features for getting list of users a client has and getting list of sites a client has, assuming the user is logged in with a valid JWT. Admins can give site permissions to users and I've added an admin flag to UserEntry that controls this, and clientDatabaseEditor now supports the creation of admins, as does the command line tool
Added API for sites that allows you to get all labels at a site, all sensor IPs at a site, all labels for a given sensor, and a map of all IPs to the labels that sensor produces

Finished basic API that does the following: allows users to log in, change password, change account details, get a list of sites they have access to, if they are admin add and remove access for other users, get a list of reading labels at each site, get a list of sensors at each of site, get the labels for a given sensor, get a map of sensor to labels, get data for a given sensor and a given site and a given label between two given times
